OL,3,CGrass verges left uncut as No Mow May
OL,4,Ctakes root
OL,6,FSome ratepayers have been complaining
OL,7,Fthat borough councils have been
OL,8,Fletting the grass grow under their
OL,9,Ffeet ` literally.
OL,11,FGrass verges have been left uncut as
OL,12,Fmeasures to reduce costs are put in
OL,13,Fplace.
OL,15,FBut the idea of growing wildflowers to
OL,16,Ftransform the overgrown areas has
OL,17,Ftaken root and 'No Mow May' has become
OL,18,Fan annual event.
