OL,3,CGrass verges left uncut as No Mow May
OL,4,Ctakes root
OL,6,FDepending on how green-fingered you
OL,7,Fare - mowing the lawn can be either a
OL,8,Fchore or therapeutic.
OL,10,FEither way, it seems, nature will love
OL,11,Fit if you leave your grass uncut, or
OL,12,Fat least a patch of it, to grow wild
OL,13,Fthis month.
OL,15,FRobbie Lynn is a gardener by
OL,16,Fprofession. He owns Premier Lawns and
OL,17,Fknows a thing or two about mowing
OL,18,Fgrass.
OL,1,Wj5k7j5                          G2/7
